The paper deals with natural language processing and information extraction from scientific publications, which are common topics in the fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL). The use of clustering techniques and Open Information Extraction (OpenIE) also suggests a focus on unsupervised and semi-supervised learning methods, which are commonly used in these sub-fields.
